step1:

 Create an EC2 Instance

step2:

Access the EC2 instance through Terminal with the publicip address (personally i use mobaxterm)

step3:

Install Java(jdk) run the command   Sudo apt install openjdk-11-jdk (Need to have java to install jenkins) 

step4:

Now intall Jenkins, refer https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing for installation 

Step5:

Access Jenkins by entering the publicip address with the jenkins port in the tab 

step6:

Great, now jenkins is accessed and provide the command in terminal to get password (cat /path/)  and paste the password in the terminal, 
  install suggested plugins and Jenkins is ready to perform the tasks.

